data.description:
Custom four bedroom, three and one half bath home with two car attached and one car detached garage, sited on 3.03 acres in the Hanover school district. This home was renovated in 2015 to include updated kitchen and bathrooms. Bring your dogs and feel safe with a 6 foot VInyl privacy fence added in 2019, Brand new asphalt driveway, new Thompson Creek custom windows and a new roof on all structures with skylights the end of 2022. The first floor offers a large living room,eat-in kitchen with stainless steel appliances, granite counter tops and custom built in cabinets; dining room,family room, first floor master bedroom with attached sitting room and updated master bathroom,an additional bedroom on the first floor,hall bathroom and utility room. The second floor offers two enormous bedrooms a recreation room and a hall bathroom. Additional features include a 30 x 12 Florida room, 24 x 28 attached garage, 16 x 24 detached garage which has been finished into a living space but can easily be converted back into a garage, and a 12 x 16 storage shed. This home truly has something for everyone. 
The neighborhood is quiet and well taken care of with incredible neighbors who really make it feel like home. 

If you are a veteran, there is an option to do a VA Assumption on this home at 3% interest. Please contact for complete details.
data.whatILove: I love the natural feel of the trees and outdoor space. The neighborhood is quiet and friendly. Being military feeling at home doesn’t come easy, but this place always feels like home.
